BEGIN_PGML

>>[@ image( "UBC-SM-18-023.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*<<

A concrete drill has a uniform drill bit [`AE`] with approximately circular cross-section of radius [`a = [$a]`] [`mm`] and length [`2L = [$l*2]`] [`m`]. When a hole [`BE`] of depth [`L = [$l]`] [`m`] is drilled in a block of concrete, the drill bit experiences a uniform resistance (due to firm contact with the hole) of [`q=[$q]`] [`Nm/m`]. In addition, the hole exerts a resistance torque of [`T_e`] at the end [`E`] of the drill bit due to the drilling action. The motor of the drill applies a torque [`T_m=[$tm]`] [`Nm`] on the drill bit at [`A`] (see the figure above). Assume the shear modulus of the drill bit is [`[$g]`] [`GPa`].
Determine:
1.	The end torque [`T_e`]
2.	The maximum shear stress [`\tau_{max}`] in the drill bit
3.	The maximum shear stress [`\tau_{e_{max}}`] at the end of the drill bit
4.	The total angle of twist [`\phi`] of the drill bit. 

[`T_e=`] [_____]{"$te"} [`Nm`]  
[`\tau_{max}=`] [_____]{"$taumax"} [`MPa`]  
[`\tau_{e_{max}}=`] [_____]{"$tauemax"} [`MPa`]  
[`\phi=`] [_____]{"$phi"}[`^{\circ}`]  

